RE POINTS:<br>
Good job VI, there is SOME incentive now to try and kill those who are within your OWN level range.  It doesnt mean you cant still kill newbs if you want, you CAN.  You just affect your teams points if you do.  If you care about that, you wont kill many newbs, if you dont care about that, you will kill newbs anyway (to show what a kickass PvP player you are). <br>
<br>
RE SPELLS: <br>
Good job VI, spells SHOULD affect all players, a wiz ice-comet is still going to one-shot a lvl 25 or lower player, but at least if you have 6 level 25 players, the wiz will think twice about attacking, for fear of being run OOM, and then stunned(keeping him from gating), and then beat down by the melees.  So, in other words, be a little more careful in how you PvP.  <br>
<br>
You should NOT be allowed to just walk into a zone of 50+ people, alone, and just say &quot;Im here, and none of you can do anything about it!!  Im gonna kill you as I see you because Im SUPERMAN, no strategy in the world can hurt me, because Im so much higher than you!!&quot;  You should be forced to use SOME strategy, even if you do outlevel someone else.  Allowing the use of spells to affect other higher levels helps low levels to defend themselves with STRATEGY, against higher levels who come into a zone using NO STRATEGY. <br>
